1
00:00:10,145 --> 00:00:11,825
Why do we get to have fun out here today?

2
00:00:16,065 --> 00:00:17,385
Who said we’re here for fun?

3
00:00:17,545 --> 00:00:20,384
Comrade Ploeng trusted you to reach the villagers.

4
00:00:20,385 --> 00:00:21,984
We’re here to work.

5
00:00:21,985 --> 00:00:24,344
Yeah, I know. I'm just messing with you.

6
00:00:24,345 --> 00:00:26,441
Our job is to get as many villagers on our side as possible.

7
00:00:26,465 --> 00:00:28,705
The more people trust us, the faster we win.

8
00:00:29,785 --> 00:00:31,745
If you want to gain people's trust,

9
00:00:32,305 --> 00:00:33,585
you must know how to give first.

10
00:00:33,985 --> 00:00:36,705
If you just walk in like that, why would anyone follow you?

11
00:00:36,945 --> 00:00:37,945
Give?

12
00:00:38,305 --> 00:00:41,625
We barely even have meat to eat. What can we give?

13
00:00:44,985 --> 00:00:48,984
Give what you can. Eat just enough. Use just enough.

14
00:00:48,985 --> 00:00:50,384
Share whatever’s left with others.

15
00:00:50,385 --> 00:00:52,624
If there is nothing to give, you give them a hand.

16
00:00:52,625 --> 00:00:55,585
It’s that simple. Students like you should understand that.

17
00:00:58,185 --> 00:00:59,625
Hey! Help!

18
00:01:01,265 --> 00:01:02,504
Help!

19
00:01:02,505 --> 00:01:03,505
Help! Please help my son!

20
00:01:04,945 --> 00:01:05,945
Help! Please help my son!

21
00:01:06,945 --> 00:01:09,425
Please help, my son is dying!

22
00:01:11,145 --> 00:01:12,225
Lead the way, sir.

23
00:01:13,545 --> 00:01:14,545
This way.

24
00:01:14,705 --> 00:01:18,304
Aaaah! (crying)

25
00:01:18,305 --> 00:01:19,305
Yaguar!

26
00:01:19,545 --> 00:01:22,544
We can only clean the wound and apply herbs.

27
00:01:22,545 --> 00:01:22,905
Yes.

28
00:01:23,465 --> 00:01:25,304
What happened to his son?

29
00:01:25,305 --> 00:01:26,025
An explosion.

30
00:01:26,026 --> 00:01:27,144
What? An explosion?!

31
00:01:27,145 --> 00:01:28,624
He stepped on it while gathering bamboo shoots

32
00:01:28,625 --> 00:01:29,744
in the forest yesterday.

33
00:01:29,745 --> 00:01:30,745
Yesterday?

34
00:01:30,945 --> 00:01:32,784
Then why didn’t you take him to a hospital?

35
00:01:32,785 --> 00:01:34,224
Or a clinic in town?

36
00:01:34,225 --> 00:01:36,664
He’d die on the way before we even get there.

37
00:01:36,665 --> 00:01:38,824
They don’t have money. No ID cards.

38
00:01:38,825 --> 00:01:40,185
No one cares about them.

39
00:01:40,865 --> 00:01:42,745
We’ll do what we can with the medicine we have.

40
00:01:45,385 --> 00:01:47,625
Aaah…! (in pain)

41
00:01:48,065 --> 00:01:53,665
Aaah…!

42
00:02:00,745 --> 00:02:01,345
Are you scared!

43
00:02:01,346 --> 00:02:02,984
Aaah…! (in pain)

44
00:02:02,985 --> 00:02:05,145
Aaah…!

45
00:02:07,745 --> 00:02:09,185
I know this place is far.

46
00:02:10,585 --> 00:02:12,865
But if they want to see a doctor, they should be able to.

47
00:02:17,225 --> 00:02:18,864
When I went on volunteer camps,

48
00:02:18,865 --> 00:02:20,465
I saw inequality everywhere.

49
00:02:22,985 --> 00:02:24,385
But this place is on another level.

50
00:02:31,865 --> 00:02:32,945
Are you listening?

51
00:02:42,345 --> 00:02:44,185
I used to be like you.

52
00:02:46,545 --> 00:02:48,785
But getting angry doesn’t fix anything.

53
00:02:50,905 --> 00:02:55,705
Better to use that anger to help people.

54
00:02:57,985 --> 00:03:00,865
And don’t let your it follow you into your dreams.

55
00:03:03,065 --> 00:03:05,345
Do I really look that weak?

56
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,785
And just now…

57
00:03:12,065 --> 00:03:13,465
Who was the one hiding behind me?

58
00:03:15,505 --> 00:03:17,945
Being scared isn’t something to be ashamed of.

59
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:21,585
I wasn't scared. Just a little startled.

60
00:03:21,705 --> 00:03:22,745
Aaaah!!!

61
00:03:23,705 --> 00:03:24,745
Aaaah!!!

62
00:03:26,465 --> 00:03:31,105
Aaaah!!!

63
00:04:16,785 --> 00:04:19,184
Uncle, please go tell all other fellow villagers

64
00:04:19,185 --> 00:04:21,945
that the comrades in the forest are ready to help everyone.

65
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:23,864
No matter what happens,

66
00:04:23,865 --> 00:04:26,025
we’ll always stand by the people.

67
00:04:26,745 --> 00:04:27,745
Okay.

68
00:04:28,945 --> 00:04:31,144
Here, this is pain killer.

69
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:33,144
Take two pills when it hurts.

70
00:04:33,145 --> 00:04:34,305
I’m giving you eight tablets.

71
00:04:36,785 --> 00:04:37,785
Thank you so much.

72
00:04:42,785 --> 00:04:45,064
Well, I’ll go check on my mom now.

73
00:04:45,065 --> 00:04:48,704
Comrade Roong… do you have any medicine left?

74
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:51,225
Don’t worry, I prepared some already.

75
00:04:52,105 --> 00:04:53,744
But I can’t go with you today.

76
00:04:53,745 --> 00:04:55,744
I have to return to base. Some unfinished business.

77
00:04:55,745 --> 00:04:56,745
That’s totally fine.

78
00:04:56,746 --> 00:04:58,825
You’ve been of great help already. Thank you.

79
00:05:01,905 --> 00:05:03,304
I want to visit Yaguar’s mother.

80
00:05:03,305 --> 00:05:04,464
Let’s go together.

81
00:05:04,465 --> 00:05:05,465
Comrade Roong!

82
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:07,785
You’re heading back, right? I’ll go with you.

83
00:05:08,745 --> 00:05:09,905
I need to finish my article.

84
00:05:10,265 --> 00:05:11,265
Alright.

85
00:05:26,225 --> 00:05:29,305
Comrade Roong sent some fever and cough medicine for you, mom.

86
00:05:30,065 --> 00:05:32,304
But she's busy so she couldn’t come herself.

87
00:05:32,305 --> 00:05:35,224
And this is Comrade Ying and Comrade Saeng

88
00:05:35,225 --> 00:05:36,065
the ones I told you about.

89
00:05:36,066 --> 00:05:37,104
Hello, ma'am.

90
00:05:37,105 --> 00:05:40,704
Thank you, dear. Bless you.

91
00:05:40,705 --> 00:05:41,705
Thank you, ma’am.

92
00:05:42,825 --> 00:05:44,624
How are you feeling?

93
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:48,625
Fever and coughing on and off for about a month now.

94
00:05:49,345 --> 00:05:53,025
Chronic symptoms like this need a proper check-up.

95
00:05:53,985 --> 00:05:56,784
Comrade Roong thinks it might be tuberculosis.

96
00:05:56,785 --> 00:05:58,744
It needs continuous treatment.

97
00:05:58,745 --> 00:06:01,664
And we don’t have medicine for that at the base.

98
00:06:01,665 --> 00:06:02,825
I’m saving money, though.

99
00:06:05,025 --> 00:06:06,025
Thank you.

100
00:06:07,225 --> 00:06:08,705
Eat first, mom.

101
00:06:09,345 --> 00:06:10,505
Here, let me help you.

102
00:06:15,065 --> 00:06:16,544
Back when I was a student.

103
00:06:16,545 --> 00:06:18,865
Some seniors volunteered with doctors up in the mountains.

104
00:06:19,105 --> 00:06:20,424
Do you have that here, Yaguar?

105
00:06:20,425 --> 00:06:23,864
Used to. about two years ago.

106
00:06:23,865 --> 00:06:25,065
Two years ago?

107
00:06:34,785 --> 00:06:38,344
Then what do the villagers do without doctors?

108
00:06:38,345 --> 00:06:41,665
They go into the forest to gather herbs to make medicine.

109
00:07:08,985 --> 00:07:09,985
Anyone home?

110
00:07:16,745 --> 00:07:18,065
Anyone here?

111
00:07:21,465 --> 00:07:22,465
Yaguar.

112
00:07:29,585 --> 00:07:30,945
Is your mother feeling better?

113
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:34,664
You already saved my mother.

114
00:07:34,665 --> 00:07:36,344
I owe you more than I can repay.

115
00:07:36,345 --> 00:07:37,785
And now you’re bringing more things.

116
00:07:37,985 --> 00:07:39,264
I can’t accept this.

117
00:07:39,265 --> 00:07:42,025
Just take it. It’s only some fruit. Nothing much at all.

118
00:07:42,705 --> 00:07:43,945
Besides, the reason I came here

119
00:07:44,305 --> 00:07:46,241
is to talk to the village head about the farmland.

120
00:07:46,265 --> 00:07:47,105
Farmland?

121
00:07:47,105 --> 00:07:48,105
Yup.

122
00:07:49,305 --> 00:07:51,584
I’m planning to buy the field at the end of the village.

123
00:07:51,585 --> 00:07:53,344
But it's my rice field there now.

124
00:07:53,345 --> 00:07:55,745
Yaguar, I’m not kicking you out.

125
00:07:56,585 --> 00:07:58,945
It’s just a change of ownership. Everything stays the same.

126
00:08:00,945 --> 00:08:03,265
In fact… it might even be better.

127
00:08:06,465 --> 00:08:09,144
If I lose that land… I don’t know how I’ll survive anymore.

128
00:08:09,145 --> 00:08:10,624
I’ll never forget this kindness.

129
00:08:10,625 --> 00:08:11,784
Thank you so much.

130
00:08:11,785 --> 00:08:13,824
Anything I can do for you at all, please tell me.

131
00:08:13,825 --> 00:08:14,825
Yaguar,

132
00:08:15,145 --> 00:08:16,665
I’m not going to make you do anything.

133
00:08:17,985 --> 00:08:19,785
I just need a little hand is all.

134
00:09:36,705 --> 00:09:38,305
Why are you sneaking off for a nap here?

135
00:09:39,105 --> 00:09:40,304
It's only just the first day visiting the villagers

136
00:09:40,305 --> 00:09:41,744
and you’re already dozing off?

137
00:09:41,745 --> 00:09:43,665
How would you even be able to go to battle then?

138
00:09:44,745 --> 00:09:45,865
I wasn’t sleeping.

139
00:09:46,745 --> 00:09:48,905
I was just resting my eyes.

140
00:09:49,985 --> 00:09:51,665
Besides, I’d fight my ass off if I had to.

141
00:09:53,345 --> 00:09:56,104
If you don’t want to be in the combat unit, just say it.

142
00:09:56,105 --> 00:09:57,184
No pressure.

143
00:09:57,185 --> 00:09:58,784
I’m willing to.

144
00:09:58,785 --> 00:10:00,385
The more people we have carrying guns,

145
00:10:00,745 --> 00:10:02,265
the sooner we all get to go home.

146
00:10:04,785 --> 00:10:06,344
Maybe it’s in my blood.

147
00:10:06,345 --> 00:10:08,385
I keep putting myself in dangerous situations.

148
00:10:09,465 --> 00:10:11,025
No one shares their private lives here.

149
00:10:11,825 --> 00:10:13,465
If you don’t want to hear it, then don’t.

150
00:10:16,105 --> 00:10:17,465
You want to be like your father?

151
00:10:27,145 --> 00:10:28,825
I don’t want to be like him.

152
00:10:30,025 --> 00:10:31,545
My father passed away a long time ago.

153
00:10:36,305 --> 00:10:37,865
Mine too.

154
00:10:44,945 --> 00:10:46,265
With a skilled comrade like you,

155
00:10:46,825 --> 00:10:48,145
I’m not dying that easy.

156
00:10:49,865 --> 00:10:51,744
Now that you're with me.

157
00:10:51,745 --> 00:10:54,144
If soldiers come, I’ll just hide behind a soldier.

158
00:10:54,145 --> 00:10:58,185
I mean, behind you. I’ll survive just fine.

159
00:10:59,705 --> 00:11:01,225
You better avoid the front lines then.

160
00:11:01,585 --> 00:11:03,065
I don’t feel like taking care of you.

161
00:11:06,665 --> 00:11:08,424
How can you put me in the back?

162
00:11:08,425 --> 00:11:11,705
For someone this good like me.

163
00:11:12,465 --> 00:11:13,905
That'd be a waste.

164
00:11:31,625 --> 00:11:32,625
Comrade Gaun Hin.

165
00:11:34,385 --> 00:11:37,305
So here you are. I’ve been looking everywhere for you.

166
00:11:40,505 --> 00:11:42,545
Thought you were sick. You didn’t show up for food.

167
00:11:42,745 --> 00:11:43,865
The work’s not finished yet.

168
00:11:44,585 --> 00:11:45,665
I’ll come once I’m done.

169
00:11:48,345 --> 00:11:49,745
It’s already too late now. 67.

170
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:53,185
You know we have to eat on time here.

171
00:11:53,985 --> 00:11:56,264
It's just that yesterday visit to the villagers,

172
00:11:56,265 --> 00:11:57,505
It gave me tons to write about.

173
00:12:00,385 --> 00:12:02,464
Wait till you read it, Comrade Saeng.

174
00:12:02,465 --> 00:12:05,665
This issue’s going to be a hit.

175
00:12:08,265 --> 00:12:09,265
Hey, Sila.

176
00:12:09,465 --> 00:12:10,465
Lemme ask you something.

177
00:12:11,945 --> 00:12:13,585
Do you still see Mada as your girlfriend?

178
00:12:15,065 --> 00:12:18,784
You’re so distant. Like you don’t even know each other.

179
00:12:18,785 --> 00:12:21,385
Did you forget Comrade Ploeng’s Three Delays Policy?

180
00:12:22,305 --> 00:12:25,064
We came to the forest to serve collectively.

181
00:12:25,065 --> 00:12:27,744
Ideology comes first. Love comes later.

182
00:12:27,745 --> 00:12:28,745
Don’t you remember?

183
00:12:30,465 --> 00:12:31,584
Go tell Mada then.

184
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,944
That you chose ideology over love.

185
00:12:33,945 --> 00:12:35,904
But you need to know your place, don’t you?

186
00:12:35,905 --> 00:12:37,544
You don’t have to say everything out loud.

187
00:12:37,545 --> 00:12:38,985
Acting childish like this.

188
00:12:39,345 --> 00:12:41,305
How are you going to achieve anything big?

189
00:12:42,705 --> 00:12:45,705
Besides, in here you’re Comrade Saeng.

190
00:12:46,145 --> 00:12:47,824
I’m Comrade Gaun Hin.

191
00:12:47,825 --> 00:12:49,545
Please use the right names.

192
00:12:51,705 --> 00:12:52,705
What’s up with you?

193
00:12:53,585 --> 00:12:56,264
So to do something big, we have to forget who we are?

194
00:12:56,265 --> 00:12:57,384
Forget what we’ve felt?

195
00:12:57,385 --> 00:13:00,264
Love and ideology can go together, you know.

196
00:13:00,265 --> 00:13:01,841
Time to go to the training now, shall we?

197
00:13:01,865 --> 00:13:03,545
Comrade Yue’s been waiting forever by now.

198
00:13:05,745 --> 00:13:06,784
I'll leave you alone here then.

199
00:13:06,785 --> 00:13:07,785
Suit yourself.

200
00:13:39,505 --> 00:13:42,145
Easy… hold it steady.

201
00:13:44,065 --> 00:13:45,145
Lower the barrel a bit.

202
00:13:47,345 --> 00:13:52,345
Now take a deep breath. And slowly exhale.

203
00:13:55,225 --> 00:13:56,425
Hold it.

204
00:14:20,585 --> 00:14:22,345
When was the last time you washed your hair?

205
00:14:27,425 --> 00:14:29,185
You made me run so many rounds this morning.

206
00:14:29,585 --> 00:14:30,824
Of course I smell like sweat.

207
00:14:30,825 --> 00:14:31,825
Then step back.

208
00:14:41,305 --> 00:14:42,825
If something’s bothering you, say it.

209
00:14:43,585 --> 00:14:45,585
Otherwise, you won’t hit your target today.

210
00:14:50,585 --> 00:14:53,665
Sila—uh, I mean Comrade Gaun Hin…

211
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:56,801
He’s been acting really different lately.

212
00:14:56,825 --> 00:14:58,425
Like I’m not even his friend anymore.

213
00:14:59,545 --> 00:15:02,265
And so is Comrade Ying. She’s acting strange.

214
00:15:03,145 --> 00:15:04,785
Cause you guys don't talk things through.

215
00:15:09,585 --> 00:15:13,745
Your friends might just be focused on their goals.

216
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:19,825
Setting everything else aside.

217
00:15:25,425 --> 00:15:27,825
Just like when you’re aiming forward,

218
00:15:28,865 --> 00:15:30,145
you don’t see what’s around you.

219
00:15:34,345 --> 00:15:35,985
But you don't have to push people away.

220
00:15:37,105 --> 00:15:39,424
You don’t aim your gun all the time.

221
00:15:39,425 --> 00:15:40,425
Or do you?

222
00:15:41,185 --> 00:15:42,625
You need breaks too.

223
00:15:43,785 --> 00:15:45,704
If this keeps going,

224
00:15:45,705 --> 00:15:47,305
those two might actually break up.

225
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:51,705
All you can do is look out from a distance.

226
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,344
It's okay to be worried.

227
00:15:54,345 --> 00:15:57,985
But not so worried that it messes you up.

228
00:16:05,545 --> 00:16:07,185
Go to sleep.

229
00:16:27,145 --> 00:16:28,425
Take a seat.

230
00:16:32,425 --> 00:16:34,025
We successfully took Baan Prongdong.

231
00:16:34,505 --> 00:16:36,905
Next mission: Baan Saeng Dao.

232
00:16:37,465 --> 00:16:40,145
Last stop before the northern headquarter.

233
00:16:41,265 --> 00:16:42,945
I have an informant inside Baan Saeng Dao.

234
00:16:43,505 --> 00:16:44,744
Taking that base shouldn’t be difficult.

235
00:16:44,745 --> 00:16:48,065
Yang Sue only gets surface-level intel.

236
00:16:48,585 --> 00:16:50,185
Nothing from the inside.

237
00:16:50,705 --> 00:16:52,705
I have someone that could breach in..

238
00:16:53,705 --> 00:16:55,905
But I need a bit more time to win his trust.

239
00:16:56,945 --> 00:16:58,625
What an effort,

240
00:16:59,225 --> 00:17:01,745
General Khong Khai must be proud of his son.

241
00:17:03,425 --> 00:17:04,425
Yes, sir.

242
00:17:06,425 --> 00:17:10,705
Given that, may I be assigned to Baan Prongdong?

243
00:17:11,465 --> 00:17:13,344
My informant is in that area.

244
00:17:13,345 --> 00:17:14,665
It’ll be easier to coordinate.

245
00:17:16,385 --> 00:17:18,744
Don’t mess this up, Dan Din.

246
00:17:18,745 --> 00:17:21,585
I’m counting on you for this mission.

247
00:17:23,345 --> 00:17:24,345
Understood, sir.

248
00:17:52,825 --> 00:17:57,585
Yes! I did it! I did it! I did it!!

249
00:17:58,265 --> 00:17:59,385
Woohoo!

250
00:18:00,465 --> 00:18:02,625
I did it. I actually did it!

251
00:18:03,585 --> 00:18:04,985
Nice one, Comrade Saeng.

252
00:18:07,105 --> 00:18:09,545
Good teacher makes a fast learner.

253
00:18:24,105 --> 00:18:28,224
Hey what are you doing? I’m not dead yet.

254
00:18:28,225 --> 00:18:30,745
Thought you were holding your breath with me.

255
00:18:32,025 --> 00:18:35,145
Keep training. One hit and you start bragging?

256
00:18:36,585 --> 00:18:37,785
Will do, sirrr.

257
00:19:01,065 --> 00:19:03,825
Focus. This isn’t a toy.

258
00:19:04,865 --> 00:19:06,504
I can’t chop firewood.

259
00:19:06,505 --> 00:19:08,305
I’m better at using my brain.

260
00:19:09,305 --> 00:19:11,505
Whether it’s strength or brains, it’s the same.

261
00:19:12,465 --> 00:19:15,185
With that attitude, you shouldn’t be writing anything at all.

262
00:19:16,305 --> 00:19:17,865
Keep chopping until you can do it.

263
00:19:18,745 --> 00:19:21,425
Even if I chop all day and night, I'm getting nowhere.

264
00:19:24,225 --> 00:19:25,225
Comrade Fah.

265
00:19:25,825 --> 00:19:29,385
If Comrade Gaun Hin can’t do it, show him how.

266
00:19:33,825 --> 00:19:39,465
Comrade Ploeng. Comrade Ploeng. Comrade.

267
00:19:39,785 --> 00:19:40,985
What is it?

268
00:19:42,985 --> 00:19:45,185
We got news from headquarter.

269
00:19:56,065 --> 00:19:57,625
What's wrong, dad?

270
00:20:00,305 --> 00:20:01,665
I'm fine, dear.

271
00:20:06,825 --> 00:20:09,144
The headquarter ordered us to retake Baan Prongdong

272
00:20:09,145 --> 00:20:10,625
from the soldiers.

273
00:20:11,065 --> 00:20:13,264
Even Baan Prongdong, which was better prepared than us,

274
00:20:13,265 --> 00:20:14,625
Still surrendered to the soldiers.

275
00:20:14,945 --> 00:20:16,865
So why are we being sent into risk?

276
00:20:17,985 --> 00:20:19,824
Though we're only a few of us,

277
00:20:19,825 --> 00:20:21,825
our combat units are all highly skilled.

278
00:20:22,265 --> 00:20:25,345
We minimize direct clashes. Keep it tight.

279
00:20:26,025 --> 00:20:29,024
Comrade Yue, prepare the snipers.

280
00:20:29,025 --> 00:20:30,545
We’ll ambush.

281
00:20:38,145 --> 00:20:39,784
May I request more man power?

282
00:20:39,785 --> 00:20:40,825
More man power?

283
00:20:44,665 --> 00:20:45,945
From which unit?

284
00:20:49,065 --> 00:20:52,905
If you have someone in mind, say it.

285
00:21:08,825 --> 00:21:10,225
Going to bathe?

286
00:21:13,945 --> 00:21:18,785
The water’s nice and cold. I'm fresh out of the water.

287
00:21:32,145 --> 00:21:33,145
Vin!

288
00:21:37,065 --> 00:21:38,545
What is it, Comrade Gaun Hin?

289
00:21:40,985 --> 00:21:42,545
Are you ready?

290
00:21:47,745 --> 00:21:49,784
I am as I am and always have been.

291
00:21:49,785 --> 00:21:52,985
And you…already know me well.

292
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:56,585
If it’s too much.

293
00:21:59,825 --> 00:22:01,625
I’ll try to do better then.

294
00:23:20,585 --> 00:23:24,865
Get ready. Tomorrow, you'll be stuck with me.

295
00:23:27,065 --> 00:23:30,025
Wait, what?

296
00:23:31,785 --> 00:23:32,785
I mean to the battle.

297
00:23:41,385 --> 00:23:42,985
Not bathing?

298
00:24:08,265 --> 00:24:10,904
Boiled water. Carry it with you.

299
00:24:10,905 --> 00:24:12,505
To keep hydrated on the way.

300
00:24:16,225 --> 00:24:17,225
Cold?

301
00:24:18,425 --> 00:24:21,265
I chilled it by the stream. Nice and refreshing.

302
00:24:23,985 --> 00:24:25,985
Come back safe, Comrade Yue.

303
00:24:37,345 --> 00:24:38,704
Good luck, bro.

304
00:24:38,705 --> 00:24:41,465
You’re the first in our batch to go into battle.

305
00:24:42,625 --> 00:24:43,625
Thanks.

306
00:24:46,745 --> 00:24:49,865
You don’t have to win. Just come back safe.

307
00:24:50,345 --> 00:24:51,345
Piece of cake.

308
00:24:52,025 --> 00:24:54,144
As if I'm just going to shooting range.

309
00:24:54,145 --> 00:24:55,425
I’ll be back in no time.

310
00:24:56,305 --> 00:24:58,105
You’ve got this, Comrade Saeng.

311
00:25:01,585 --> 00:25:04,065
Come on, let’s go see the others.

312
00:25:14,225 --> 00:25:17,065
Have some water. It’ll refresh you.

313
00:25:19,145 --> 00:25:20,305
Nice and cold.

314
00:25:30,945 --> 00:25:31,985
So refreshing.

315
00:25:37,025 --> 00:25:40,184
Now our Baan Prongdong has been crushed by the soldiers.

316
00:25:40,185 --> 00:25:42,264
Their bullets. Their bombs.

317
00:25:42,265 --> 00:25:44,464
We will reclaim our honor.

318
00:25:44,465 --> 00:25:46,425
We will take back Baan Prongdong.

319
00:25:46,825 --> 00:25:48,984
Not just as a base—.

320
00:25:48,985 --> 00:25:51,704
But as the heart of the people.

321
00:25:51,705 --> 00:25:54,984
All units heading into battle today—.

322
00:25:54,985 --> 00:26:00,744
Follow Comrade Yue’s orders. And remember.

323
00:26:00,745 --> 00:26:04,304
That victory is waiting for us ahead.

324
00:26:04,305 --> 00:26:06,064
Hey!!!

325
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:09,225
Sniper, take your position here. Find your right spot.

326
00:26:10,185 --> 00:26:11,384
Take down as many soldiers as possible.

327
00:26:11,385 --> 00:26:12,745
Minimize direct engagement.

328
00:26:14,185 --> 00:26:15,385
Can we not kill?

329
00:26:18,345 --> 00:26:20,265
This is war, not a trip.

330
00:26:21,225 --> 00:26:22,785
Get to your position.

331
00:26:28,785 --> 00:26:30,305
If you don’t want to kill

332
00:26:32,185 --> 00:26:36,024
just make sure they can’t pick up a gun again.

333
00:26:36,025 --> 00:26:37,504
Follow my orders.

334
00:26:37,505 --> 00:26:41,465
No matter what happens, do not leave your cover.

335
00:26:42,945 --> 00:26:44,465
Not until it’s over.

336
00:26:53,465 --> 00:26:54,905
Do you want to retreat?

337
00:26:57,105 --> 00:27:01,025
I’m scared. But I won’t run.

338
00:27:02,545 --> 00:27:07,025
We’ll win together. Trust me.

339
00:27:20,425 --> 00:27:21,425
Sergeant.

340
00:27:21,665 --> 00:27:22,665
Yes, sir.

341
00:27:23,265 --> 00:27:26,385
Status? See anything fishy?

342
00:27:27,825 --> 00:27:28,825
All clear.

343
00:27:30,145 --> 00:27:32,905
Sir, any word from the northern unit?

344
00:27:35,305 --> 00:27:38,625
Just in. They can’t send supply unit for the next two days.

345
00:27:39,065 --> 00:27:40,065
Damn.

346
00:27:40,945 --> 00:27:43,945
If they attack now, we’re almost out of ammo.

347
00:27:45,385 --> 00:27:49,265
I’ll handle that myself. Don’t worry.

348
00:28:23,025 --> 00:28:24,745
Aaah!!

349
00:29:22,145 --> 00:29:23,345
Comrade Saeng!

350
00:29:48,625 --> 00:29:51,985
Coordinates 34. we’re under attack. Requesting retreat.

351
00:29:54,705 --> 00:29:55,705
Fall back!!

352
00:29:59,345 --> 00:30:00,345
Comrade Saeng.

353
00:30:01,505 --> 00:30:05,864
Blood blood! Comrade Yue, are you okay?!

354
00:30:05,865 --> 00:30:07,704
I’m fine. That’s not my blood.

355
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:08,705
Comrade Saeng.

356
00:30:12,425 --> 00:30:13,425
I killed a person.

357
00:30:14,305 --> 00:30:16,144
You saved my life, Comrade Saeng.

358
00:30:16,145 --> 00:30:17,145
I killed a person.

359
00:30:18,425 --> 00:30:21,625
It’s over… it’s all over now, Comrade Saeng.

360
00:30:23,025 --> 00:30:24,265
I killed a person.

361
00:30:25,785 --> 00:30:29,305
This isn't how I wanted it. This isn't how I wanted it to be.

362
00:30:30,265 --> 00:30:31,305
It’s over, Comrade Saeng…

363
00:30:45,345 --> 00:30:46,665
The combat unit is back!

364
00:30:47,865 --> 00:30:49,265
Everyone listen!

365
00:30:50,505 --> 00:30:52,464
Victory's ours.

366
00:30:52,465 --> 00:30:54,385
Yeah!!

367
00:30:55,545 --> 00:30:56,545
Great job, everyone!

368
00:30:56,545 --> 00:30:57,545
Comrade Ploeng.

369
00:30:57,825 --> 00:31:00,064
Comrade Saeng shot the enemy commander

370
00:31:00,065 --> 00:31:00,785
right in the forehead.

371
00:31:00,786 --> 00:31:02,105
One shot. Down instantly.

372
00:31:02,505 --> 00:31:04,745
Right in the forehead?

373
00:31:06,025 --> 00:31:08,224
- Comrade Saeng is incredible.
- Ow—.

374
00:31:08,225 --> 00:31:11,584
Comrade Baitong, easy. He just got shot.

375
00:31:11,585 --> 00:31:14,505
Comrade Roong, come check on him please.

376
00:31:15,065 --> 00:31:16,745
I’m fine. It just grazed me.

377
00:31:17,265 --> 00:31:19,025
No, you still need treatment.

378
00:31:20,185 --> 00:31:21,544
Comrade Roong, go prepare the supplies.

379
00:31:21,545 --> 00:31:22,785
I’ll take him to the infirmary.

380
00:31:23,625 --> 00:31:24,625
Yes.

381
00:31:25,945 --> 00:31:27,225
Do I really have to…?

382
00:31:29,905 --> 00:31:31,425
Is it going to hurt?

383
00:31:32,985 --> 00:31:34,585
I knew I wasn’t wrong about this kid.

384
00:31:35,545 --> 00:31:37,505
His first time in battle.

385
00:31:38,545 --> 00:31:40,425
It’s not that bad.

386
00:31:46,025 --> 00:31:47,704
Treat the others outside first.

387
00:31:47,705 --> 00:31:48,865
- I'll be right after.
- Okay.

388
00:32:06,665 --> 00:32:09,065
Ah—!

389
00:32:30,745 --> 00:32:32,545
Ouchhh!!

390
00:32:55,505 --> 00:32:57,505
Don’t you ever do that again.

391
00:32:58,905 --> 00:33:02,385
In the battle field, you follow orders.

392
00:33:05,105 --> 00:33:06,105
Understand?

393
00:33:11,145 --> 00:33:12,425
But I was worried about you.

394
00:33:13,265 --> 00:33:17,584
From this heart that still holds onto your love.

395
00:33:17,585 --> 00:33:21,544
Onto the promises.

396
00:33:21,545 --> 00:33:23,744
That no matter how long it takes,

397
00:33:23,745 --> 00:33:28,185
no one could ever take your place…

398
00:33:35,665 --> 00:33:43,665
I just want to wake up without tears.

399
00:33:43,865 --> 00:33:47,664
Wishing it would all fade away.

400
00:33:47,665 --> 00:33:52,264
Begging the wind to carry it off.

401
00:33:52,265 --> 00:33:56,184
I don’t want to live like this.

402
00:33:56,185 --> 00:33:58,665
As someone who never forgets.

403
00:34:00,545 --> 00:34:04,424
I could barely breathe.

404
00:34:04,425 --> 00:34:08,305
If I knew I’d lose you…

405
00:34:10,425 --> 00:34:11,785
The first time I killed someone,

406
00:34:12,825 --> 00:34:14,665
my hands shook just like yours.

407
00:34:16,585 --> 00:34:19,105
That moment, I couldn’t even move.

408
00:34:20,465 --> 00:34:21,865
Weren’t you scared?

409
00:34:24,945 --> 00:34:26,145
Of course I was.

410
00:34:28,425 --> 00:34:29,465
But I had to do it.

411
00:34:30,585 --> 00:34:33,145
Was there... no other choice?

412
00:34:37,465 --> 00:34:38,785
Want to stay at my place?

413
00:34:40,425 --> 00:34:42,265
You won’t get any sleep in the shared quarter.

414
00:34:42,985 --> 00:34:44,905
People coming and going all day.

415
00:34:46,665 --> 00:34:52,545
It's deputy leader's place. Am I allowed?

416
00:34:59,345 --> 00:35:00,505
Why aren't you?

417
00:35:53,545 --> 00:35:54,905
News for the People
NORTHERN LIGHT.

418
00:35:58,585 --> 00:36:01,825
The hands of students ignite the people to rise…

419
00:37:08,665 --> 00:37:10,065
Another nightmare?

420
00:37:27,945 --> 00:37:31,745
I dreamed of soldiers and explosions.

421
00:37:35,545 --> 00:37:37,345
People dying right in front of me.

422
00:37:39,145 --> 00:37:40,585
Blood everywhere.

423
00:37:42,745 --> 00:37:44,225
It was terrifying.

424
00:37:48,425 --> 00:37:50,065
Why does this water taste strange?

425
00:37:51,985 --> 00:37:54,745
Homemade saline. It helps refresh you.

426
00:38:08,425 --> 00:38:09,425
Where are you going?

427
00:38:10,905 --> 00:38:12,665
I want you to get some rest.

428
00:38:14,425 --> 00:38:15,945
You’ve been helping me the whole time…

429
00:38:17,025 --> 00:38:18,344
I feel bad.

430
00:38:18,345 --> 00:38:21,545
You sleep. I'm way tougher than you.

431
00:38:22,945 --> 00:38:25,265
Going a few days without sleep is a breeze.

432
00:38:26,345 --> 00:38:29,584
Then let’s take turns. I’ll share the bed.

433
00:38:29,585 --> 00:38:31,345
I don’t want to take advantage of you.

434
00:38:32,345 --> 00:38:34,465
It’s fine. Just sleep.

435
00:39:42,865 --> 00:39:43,944
Comrade Saeng,

436
00:39:43,945 --> 00:39:47,464
a student who's just recently joined the combat unit

437
00:39:47,465 --> 00:39:49,944
exceeded expectations in his first mission.

438
00:39:49,945 --> 00:39:52,344
One Shot, One Kill: Enemy Commander Down.

439
00:39:52,345 --> 00:39:55,424
How's that? Exciting enough for a headline?

440
00:39:55,425 --> 00:39:58,785
Using someone’s death for news… You sure about that?

441
00:39:59,745 --> 00:40:02,544
But your achievement boosts everyone’s morale.

442
00:40:02,545 --> 00:40:03,545
Why are you upset?

443
00:40:03,546 --> 00:40:05,504
No matter who dies in the battle field,

444
00:40:05,505 --> 00:40:07,184
it’s all terrible.

445
00:40:07,185 --> 00:40:10,025
If we won today, but I died there,

446
00:40:11,025 --> 00:40:12,664
would you still write a headline like that?

447
00:40:12,665 --> 00:40:15,625
Comrade Saeng!! This is about morale,

448
00:40:16,465 --> 00:40:17,465
not for fun.

449
00:40:18,545 --> 00:40:21,144
We still shouldn’t treat death like this.

450
00:40:21,145 --> 00:40:22,585
Like we’re proud of killing someone.

451
00:40:23,785 --> 00:40:25,865
Hey. Comrade Saeng’s not fully recovered yet.

452
00:40:26,785 --> 00:40:27,945
You should leave.

453
00:40:47,465 --> 00:40:50,705
I don’t like the way Comrade Gaun Hin writes this.

454
00:40:52,065 --> 00:40:53,385
If their family saw it,

455
00:40:54,865 --> 00:40:56,785
how heartbroken would they feel?

456
00:41:02,625 --> 00:41:04,425
You took out their commander.

457
00:41:05,905 --> 00:41:09,545
You dealed with it before the battle gets out of hand.

458
00:41:11,745 --> 00:41:13,865
We need the people to know that.

459
00:41:14,985 --> 00:41:17,025
Comrade Gaun Hin is just doing his job.

460
00:41:20,105 --> 00:41:23,984
In war, no one wants a death to be meaningless.

461
00:41:23,985 --> 00:41:26,544
If we don’t turn it into strength,

462
00:41:26,545 --> 00:41:28,345
how do the living move forward?

463
00:41:34,305 --> 00:41:35,825
If you could turn back time,

464
00:41:37,465 --> 00:41:38,585
would you still kill him?

465
00:41:46,545 --> 00:41:48,105
I’d do the same.

466
00:41:52,225 --> 00:41:53,705
I didn’t want you to die.

467
00:42:21,265 --> 00:42:24,105
Maybe I should go sleep in the hut tonight.

468
00:42:27,185 --> 00:42:28,305
I don’t want to trouble you.

469
00:42:32,545 --> 00:42:33,545
Stay here.

470
00:42:38,105 --> 00:42:41,065
I’ll... take care of you.

471
00:43:58,945 --> 00:44:06,945
I just want to wake up without tears…

472
00:44:07,065 --> 00:44:10,944
Wish it would all fade away.

473
00:44:10,945 --> 00:44:15,464
Begging the wind to blow it away.

474
00:44:15,465 --> 00:44:18,545
I don’t want to live like this.

475
00:44:19,265 --> 00:44:23,624
As someone who never forgets…

476
00:44:23,625 --> 00:44:25,144
I could barely breathe.

477
00:44:25,145 --> 00:44:27,264
- I could barely breathe.
- You treat me so well.

478
00:44:27,265 --> 00:44:29,824
If I knew I’d lose you…

479
00:44:29,825 --> 00:44:32,041
- If I knew I’d lose you…
- It makes it harder for me.

480
00:44:32,065 --> 00:44:40,065
I just want to wake up without tears…

481
00:44:40,385 --> 00:44:44,184
Wishing it would all fade away.

482
00:44:44,185 --> 00:44:48,664
Begging the wind to carry it off.

483
00:44:48,665 --> 00:44:51,745
I don’t want to live like this.

484
00:44:52,425 --> 00:44:56,904
As someone who never forgets…

485
00:44:56,905 --> 00:45:00,904
I could barely breathe.

486
00:45:00,905 --> 00:45:04,985
If I knew I’d lose you…

487
00:45:06,265 --> 00:45:13,504
Every night, pretending I can handle it.

488
00:45:13,505 --> 00:45:17,704
Not knowing how deep I'm sinking.

489
00:45:17,705 --> 00:45:21,504
I’d be fine.

490
00:45:21,505 --> 00:45:25,984
I told myself I could live without you…

491
00:45:25,985 --> 00:45:30,424
A world without you might feel lighter.

492
00:45:30,425 --> 00:45:36,305
But today, I realize… you've never left

